# Input
```ts
// `Id<string>` substitutes to `string`, so the indexOf comparison can use includes().
type Id<T> = T;
declare const text: Id<string>;
text.indexOf("a") !== -1;

```

# Diagnostics
```
invalidGenericTypeAlias.ts:4:1 lint/nursery/useIncludes  FIXABLE  ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  i Checking the result of indexOf() against -1 to test for presence.
  
    2 │ type Id<T> = T;
    3 │ declare const text: Id<string>;
  > 4 │ text.indexOf("a") !== -1;
      │ ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^
    5 │ 
  
  i indexOf() returns a numeric index, not a boolean. Comparing it against -1 is error-prone and harder to read.
  
  i Use includes() instead, which directly expresses the intent and returns a boolean.
  
  i This rule belongs to the nursery group, which means it is not yet stable and may change in the future. Visit https://biomejs.dev/linter/#nursery for more information.
  
  i Unsafe fix: Replace with .includes().
  
    2 2 │   type Id<T> = T;
    3 3 │   declare const text: Id<string>;
    4   │ - text.indexOf("a")·!==·-1;
      4 │ + text.includes("a");
    5 5 │   
  

```
